Dr.Tal Ben-Shahar:Hi.Good morning.
各位早上好

2
00:00:21,250 --> 00:00:23,330
Good morning.Welcome back.
早上好 很高兴又见到大家

3
00:00:24,490 --> 00:00:27,590
Hope you had a wonderful break.
希望你们都度过了一个愉快的假期

4
00:00:27,950 --> 00:00:32,230
That you took time to recover,to de-stress.
恢复元气 释放压力

5
00:00:33,750 --> 00:00:37,720
And as it happens,this is the topic today.
这也是今天的主题

6
00:00:38,280 --> 00:00:42,150
We'll continue from where we left off before break.
我们接着上节课继续讲

7
00:00:43,140 --> 00:00:47,980
So remember we talked about the idea that in fact,
上回我们提出 事实上

8
00:00:48,240 --> 00:00:50,080
stress wasn't the problem,
压力不是问题

9
00:00:50,290 --> 00:00:53,800
which was the most interesting,surprising- but in retrospect,
这是压力研究最有趣 最令人惊讶

10
00:00:54,030 --> 00:00:57,590
obvious finding of the research on stress.
现在看来 也是最显著的发现

11
00:00:57,810 --> 00:01:01,420
That stress in and of itself is actually good,
压力本身其实是件好事

12
00:01:03,030 --> 00:01:06,390
just like in athletics,just like in sports,
就像在体育运动中

13
00:01:07,790 --> 00:01:11,840
when we stress a muscle,the muscle develop- it grows.
我们给肌肉以压力 肌肉就会发展 增长

14
00:01:12,090 --> 00:01:15,750
When we stress ourselves psychologically,emotionally,we grow.
我们心理上情感上给予自己压力 我们就会成长

15
00:01:15,950 --> 00:01:19,250
We become more resilient.We become stronger.
变得更开朗 更坚强

16
00:01:19,250 --> 00:01:20,740
It's not good for a person
从小在无菌环境里长大

17
00:01:21,610 --> 00:01:25,070
who's just born to be put in a sterile environment
从未受过外界任何压力

18
00:01:25,610 --> 00:01:29,400
and be protected from all the stresses of the outside world,
对人是不利的

19
00:01:29,650 --> 00:01:33,420
such as bacteria for example,which stresses the system.
比如影响机体的细菌

20
00:01:34,140 --> 00:01:36,620
Cause it forces to grade antibodies.
会使人体产生抗体

21
00:01:37,020 --> 00:01:39,260
It's not good for us to be in a sterile environment,
所以长在无菌环境中对我们是不利的

22
00:01:39,460 --> 00:01:45,150
not physically- whether it's in a closing environment as babies,
不仅指生理上婴儿的密闭环境

23
00:01:45,430 --> 00:01:47,630
not physically in terms of not doing sports,
缺乏运动

24
00:01:47,870 --> 00:01:51,180
not pushing ourselves,and also not mentally and emotionally-
还包括心理及情感

25
00:01:51,420 --> 00:01:55,130
which is why I said you know time and again: I wish you fail more
所以我常常说 我希望你们遭受更多的失败

26
00:01:55,370 --> 00:01:57,530
Because I think it is important to go through hardships,
因为艰难困苦

27
00:01:57,770 --> 00:01:58,860
through difficulties.
能给予我们极大的锻炼

28
00:01:59,080 --> 00:02:02,060
And in fact,we are going to talk about failure
结束"目标设定"的课程后

29
00:02:02,360 --> 00:02:05,170
right after we finish up with the "Goal setting" lecture,
就会开始关于失败的课程

30
00:02:05,400 --> 00:02:07,170
when we discuss perfectionism,
我们会讨论完美主义

31
00:02:07,800 --> 00:02:10,750
which is all about our approach toward failure.
也就是对待失败的态度

32
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:15,150
So stress is not the problem.The problem is lack of recovery.
所以问题不是压力 而是缺乏休整

33
00:02:15,370 --> 00:02:19,180
And that is what we don't have enough of in our culture-
不仅仅在哈佛 我们的文化中

34
00:02:19,420 --> 00:02:20,850
not just at Harvard.
都对休息缺乏重视

35
00:02:21,330 --> 00:02:24,270
Most workplaces- there is not enough place for recovery;
大多数办公场所 都没有足够的地方进行休整

36
00:02:24,480 --> 00:02:26,920
in most school,most universities- which explains
大多数学校 大学

37
00:02:27,150 --> 00:02:32,180
why levels of stress translate themselves to chronic stress,
所以压力转变为慢性压力

38
00:02:32,430 --> 00:02:34,650
translate themselves to chronic anxiety,
变成了长期焦虑

39
00:02:34,870 --> 00:02:38,010
translate themselves to depression.
变成了抑郁症

40
00:02:38,820 --> 00:02:40,940
It's because we don't have the recovery.
就因为我们没有休整

41
00:02:41,180 --> 00:02:43,030
And we talked about recovery on the a few levels-
我们还讲了不同层面的休整

42
00:02:43,260 --> 00:02:44,690
so just a quick recap.
快速回顾一下

43
00:02:44,940 --> 00:02:48,090
We talked about recovery on the micro level,which is,
微观层面上 休整可以是

44
00:02:48,330 --> 00:02:52,690
for example,every 90 minutes of sprint,15 minutes break-
比如 每冲刺90分钟 就休息15分钟

45
00:02:53,580 --> 00:02:57,260
instead of marathon runners,being sprinters.
不要做马拉松运动员 要做短跑运动员

46
00:02:58,280 --> 00:02:59,800
It's 15 minutes meditation.
可以是15分钟冥想

47
00:03:00,060 --> 00:03:01,380
It's a one hour lunch,
一小时的午餐

48
00:03:01,650 --> 00:03:04,280
where we really give ourselves time to recover.
给自己时间好好休整

49
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:07,990
It's going to the gym on a regular basis.
可以是定期去健身房

50
00:03:08,460 --> 00:03:11,670
It's the 15 minutes of listening to our favorite piece of music,
听15分钟喜欢的音乐

51
00:03:12,110 --> 00:03:14,050
speaking to a friend or whatever it is.
与朋友聊天 等等

52
00:03:14,300 --> 00:03:15,380
The recovery on the micro level.
这是微观层面上的休整

53
00:03:15,650 --> 00:03:19,910
And people who recover,who have recovered during their work day-
上班时间进行休整的人...

54
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:22,150
and this is research done across the river
河对岸的Teresa Amabile和Leslie Perlow等人

55
00:03:22,420 --> 00:03:26,170
by people like Teresa Amabile or Leslie Perlow,
经过研究发现

56
00:03:26,460 --> 00:03:30,160
show how important it is in a workplace to have recoveries
如果工作场所能提供休整

57
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:32,640
and people who do it are more productive,
能使员工效率更高 更有创意

58
00:03:32,850 --> 00:03:36,940
more creative and in the long term,also happier.
并且长期来看 会更幸福

59
00:03:37,160 --> 00:03:39,140
Higher levels of job satisfaction.
提高工作满意度

60
00:03:39,430 --> 00:03:43,120
Recovery also on the mezzo level the full night sleep,
中度休整包括一夜好眠

61
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:47,230
the day off during once a week at least.
每周至少休息一天

62
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:52,520
Time off recreate so that we can create.
放松休息以便重新投入工作

63
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:57,430
And finally,the vacations.Holidays.Longer periods.
最后还有假期 节假日 长假

64
00:04:03,230 --> 00:04:06,780
You see,the other thing that happens
如果我们片刻不停的运作

65
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:09,110
when we are constantly on the run is that
会发生什么

66
00:04:09,330 --> 00:04:13,900
we miss the beauty that's all around us and within us.
我们错过了身边和自身的风景

67
00:04:14,190 --> 00:04:17,920
We miss the real potential for happiness,for joy,
错过了获得快乐幸福

68
00:04:18,170 --> 00:04:22,760
for appreciation that surrounds us day in and day out.
欣赏日常生活中美的机会

69
00:04:22,990 --> 00:04:24,220
And that's why we take things for granted.
所以我们把一切都当做理所当然

70
00:04:24,460 --> 00:04:29,650
Because we don't take the time to appreciate,to savor.
因为我们没有花时间去欣赏体会

71
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,680
And it's not natural to do so.
这有悖自然

72
00:04:35,940 --> 00:04:37,500
I mean can you imagine?
你们能想象

73
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:41,270
Can you imagine a lion living in our modern world?
一头狮子生活在现代世界?

74
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:45,110
Can you imagine a lion working at McKinsey?
在麦肯锡或者投资银行上班

75
00:04:45,780 --> 00:04:49,450
Or in investment banking? Or being on the tenure track?
或者成为终身教授?

76
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:55,030
It's unnatural.You know what a lion needs to do is yawn.
这很反常 大家都知道狮子要打瞌睡

77
00:04:56,180 --> 00:04:58,250
They need to play.It is natural.
要追逐嬉戏 这才正常

78
00:04:58,460 --> 00:04:59,400
And remember what we talked about
还记得我们头几节课

79
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,930
during the first couple of lectures?
怎么说的吗

80
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:04,000
The constraint view of human nature-
人性中视野的局限性

81
00:05:04,220 --> 00:05:06,080
nature to be commanded must be obeyed.
服从权力

82
00:05:06,330 --> 00:05:09,440
Our nature dictates that we need recovery.
人的天性需要休整

83
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:11,440
All animals do.
所有动物都是

84
00:05:13,670 --> 00:05:16,760
And when we frustrate a psychological,physical need,
如果我们违背心理或生理需求

85
00:05:17,050 --> 00:05:21,030
we pay a price for it,whether it's the need for recovery
就会为此付出代价 无论是需要休整

86
00:05:21,300 --> 00:05:23,500
or the need for physical exercise,
需要身体锻炼

87
00:05:24,240 --> 00:05:27,490
or the need for certain vitamins or protein.
还是需要某种维生素或蛋白质

88
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:31,280
We pay a price for it.And the key is,
我们会为此付出代价 关键是

89
00:05:31,540 --> 00:05:36,590
to introduce these natural recovery periods into our lives.
将这种本能的休整期引入我们的生活

90
00:05:40,340 --> 00:05:45,230
And here is the key.The key is focus.
关键就是集中注意

91
00:05:45,530 --> 00:05:48,870
Focus on both work as well as recovery.
同时关注工作与休整

92
00:05:49,570 --> 00:05:51,420
So remember the question that we asked before break.
想一下我们节前提出的问题

93
00:05:51,660 --> 00:05:55,880
What makes some individuals succeed despite
处于相同的现代社会 拥有相似的雄心壮志

94
00:05:56,790 --> 00:06:01,420
living in a modern world or living with ambition and success?
为什么有些人能获得成功?

95
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:05,350
Well these individuals know how to focus
他们知道

96
00:06:05,590 --> 00:06:06,830
when they work,when they play.
何时聚焦工作 何时聚焦玩乐

97
00:06:07,050 --> 00:06:09,340
To use a cliché,they work hard and they play hard.
套句老话 他们努力工作玩得开心

98
00:06:09,590 --> 00:06:15,660
What does that mean specifically? First of all,in recovery.
具体是什么意思呢?首先 要休整

99
00:06:16,220 --> 00:06:19,030
They understand that quantity affects quality.
他们明白多则劣 少则精

100
00:06:19,470 --> 00:06:23,420
Let me share with you a study that you read about in the book.
我们来看一下诺贝尔奖得主

101
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,590
This is by Nobel Prize winner,
以色列心理学家Daniel Kahneman

102
00:06:25,810 --> 00:06:29,710
the Israeli psychologist Daniel Kahneman.
进行的一项研究

103
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:34,800
Won Nobel prize for economics,turned positive psychologist.
他曾获得诺贝尔经济学奖 后来成为了积极心理学家

104
00:06:35,790 --> 00:06:37,930
What he wanted to understand was the affective,
他希望研究一天内

105
00:06:38,170 --> 00:06:40,910
the emotional experiences of women during the day.
妇女的情感感情经历

106
00:06:41,330 --> 00:06:44,930
And what he did was ask women to evaluate their experiences
他让一些妇女在经历了某些特定事件后

107
00:06:45,150 --> 00:06:47,590
right after they had that particular experience:
对此经历做出评估:

108
00:06:47,870 --> 00:06:50,100
so what was it like for you?
刚才的感觉怎么样

109
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:52,960
And they evaluated their experience at work.
这些经历包括工作

110
00:06:53,210 --> 00:06:54,950
They evaluated their experience shopping.
购物

111
00:06:55,190 --> 00:06:56,130
They evaluated their experience
与亲密伴侣 孩子

112
00:06:56,350 --> 00:07:03,620
spending time with their intimate partners,with their children,
共处的时光

113
00:07:05,650 --> 00:07:08,100
having lunch with friends,whatever it was.
与朋友共进午餐 等等

114
00:07:09,820 --> 00:07:13,160
They evaluated how they were doing during the day.
评估一天内她们的心情

115
00:07:13,400 --> 00:07:15,850
The most surprising finding of this result was that
结果令人惊讶

116
00:07:16,070 --> 00:07:18,820
these women did not particularly enjoy time
这些妇女并不特别享受

117
00:07:19,040 --> 00:07:20,810
they spent with their kids.
与孩子共处的时光

118
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:23,840
Now this result was very surprising to Kahneman.
这一结果让Kahneman很吃惊

119
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:27,520
When he probed further- he and his co-authors:
他和合作者进一步研究发现

120
00:07:28,430 --> 00:07:30,530
it wasn't the fact that the women didn't love their kids.
这些妇女并不是不爱她们的孩子

121
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:31,790
I mean they love their kids.
她们很爱孩子

122
00:07:32,010 --> 00:07:34,130
For most of these women,kids were the most meaningful,
对其中大多数人来说 孩子是她们生活中

123
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:36,530
important thing in their lives.
最有意义 最重要的一部分

124
00:07:37,010 --> 00:07:40,800
However,their experience with their kids
但是 她们与孩子共处的经历

125
00:07:41,040 --> 00:07:45,080
often was not pleasurable- the second component of happiness.
通常并不愉悦 这是快乐的第二个组成成分

126
00:07:45,360 --> 00:07:47,030
very meaningful,but not always pleasurable.
有意义但不愉悦

127
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:50,940
Why? When they probed further,they found out exactly why.
为什么呢?他们进一步研究揭露了确切的原因

128
00:07:51,170 --> 00:07:54,430
Because these women,when they were with their kids,
因为这些妇女与孩子共处时

129
00:07:54,690 --> 00:07:57,680
they were not really with their kids,
并不是真正全身心与孩子在一起

130
00:07:58,490 --> 00:08:01,140
meaning they were on the phone at the same time,
可能同时还打电话

131
00:08:01,430 --> 00:08:04,800
or doing email,or thinking about what they had,
或者写邮件

132
00:08:05,070 --> 00:08:08,170
they did earlier at work,or what they had to do later at home.
思考上班的事 或者要做的家务

133
00:08:08,520 --> 00:08:13,180
They were distracted.And they were not present with their kids.
她们一心多用 并没有全身心与孩子一起

134
00:08:13,450 --> 00:08:14,990
Now individually,discreetly,
单独来看

135
00:08:15,190 --> 00:08:17,490
they may have very enjoyed being on the phone with a friend,
她们可能和乐意与朋友讲电话

136
00:08:17,730 --> 00:08:20,800
or doing work,or thinking about work,
工作 思考工作

137
00:08:21,050 --> 00:08:23,210
or thinking about what they have to do later.
或者等下要做的事

138
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:26,970
Each discreet individual activity may have been a lot of fun.
这些活动单独发生可能很有趣

139
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:30,060
But together,it was too much of a good thing.
但是同时进行 就乐极生悲了

140
00:08:30,340 --> 00:08:33,390
And quantity affects quality.
量影响质

141
00:08:33,650 --> 00:08:36,010
I mean,thinking about the following analogy.
听听这个类比

142
00:08:36,280 --> 00:08:37,480
Think about the following analogy.
听听这个类比

143
00:08:37,720 --> 00:08:40,020
Think about your favorite piece of music
想想你闭着眼睛 全神贯注地

144
00:08:40,280 --> 00:08:43,040
and listening to it with your eyes close and focus.
听你最喜欢的音乐

145
00:08:44,610 --> 00:08:47,340
So your favorite piece of music- if it's like mine,
我最喜欢的歌是

146
00:08:47,600 --> 00:08:51,190
probably is Whitney Houston's "And I will Always Love You".
惠特尼休斯顿的《我会永远爱你》

147
00:08:53,380 --> 00:08:54,300
Thank you.Yes.
谢谢

148
00:08:54,540 --> 00:08:57,290
There's another one here with good taste in music.
英雄所见略同

149
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:01,950
And you listen to Whitney Houston
于是你听着惠特尼休斯顿的歌

150
00:09:02,130 --> 00:09:04,380
or whatever your favorite piece of music is.
或者其他你最喜欢的音乐

151
00:09:04,670 --> 00:09:06,270
You eyes close and you focus.
闭着眼睛 全神贯注

152
00:09:06,510 --> 00:09:08,460
Then you rate it on a scale of one to ten.
然后从一到十打个分数

153
00:09:09,330 --> 00:09:11,470
And of course,perfect ten: you are touched.
绝对是满分十分

154
00:09:11,740 --> 00:09:13,440
You are moved.You are inspired.
你深受感动 灵感迸发

155
00:09:14,370 --> 00:09:19,320
And then you listen to your second most favorite piece of music,
于是又开始听第二喜欢的音乐

156
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:21,230
which,if it is like mine,
如果是我

157
00:09:21,530 --> 00:09:25,080
it's the chorus piece from Beethoven's Ninth.
会选贝多芬的《第九交响曲》

158
00:09:26,260 --> 00:09:27,480
And you listen to it.You focus on it.
你全神贯注地听着

159
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:30,070
And again,you rate it on a scale of one to ten.
然后从一到十打分

160
00:09:30,330 --> 00:09:32,410
Not quite high as "And I will Always Love You",
没有《我会永远爱你》这么高

161
00:09:32,690 --> 00:09:34,060
but it's a nine and a half.
但也有9.5分了

162
00:09:34,600 --> 00:09:37,470
And then,and then,for maximum effect,
接着 为了达到最大效果

163
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:40,490
you take the two pieces together and play them.
你把两首歌同时播放

164
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:43,800
And what do you get? A nineteen and a half,right?
结果怎样? 19.5分吗

165
00:09:44,150 --> 00:09:47,750
No.Not a ten.Not even a five.It's noise.
不 不是10分 连5分也没有 纯粹是噪音

166
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:54,040
This is modern life for you.This is modern life.
这就是现代生活

167
00:09:54,470 --> 00:09:57,790
We have activities; we have so many wonderful things in our lives
我们进行各种活动 生活中有这么多美好的东西

168
00:09:58,040 --> 00:09:59,910
But we have too many of them.
但是又多过头了

169
00:10:00,390 --> 00:10:02,020
And you know what that often does?
这会怎样呢?

170
00:10:02,280 --> 00:10:04,740
It very often leads to guilt and frustration.
这常常会导致内疚 沮丧

171
